***(ABSTRACT)
*
*     JOBS REQUIRING OFFLINE TAPE OR DISK VOLUMES WILL SPECIFY THOSE
*        REQUIREMENTS VIA /*SETUP CARDS. UPON SUCCESSFUL JCL CONVERSION,
*        MESSAGES DETAILING THE JOBS SETUP REQUIREMENTS WILL BE
*        ISSUED TO THE TAPE/DISK LIBRARY CONSOLE. THE JOB STAYS IN
*        'HOLD' STATUS UNTIL ALL RESOURCES ARE ASSEMBLED FOR EXECUTION.
*     THE FOLLOWING INFORMATION WILL BE PROVIDED IN THE MSG TEXT:
*
*              JOB NUMBER
*              JOB NAME
*              EXECUTION CLASS
*              TEXT OF SETUP CARD
*              VOLSER OF DSN(IF TAPE DSN SUPPLIED IN SETUP TEXT)
*
*        ( THIS IS ST.LOUIS MODIFICTAION NUMBER 'J504' ).
*
***(LOGIC SUMMARY)
*
*  1     HASPRDR DETECTS /*SETUP, FLAGS OCCURENCE IN JQE, AND SAVES
*          IMAGE IN JCL IMAGE DATA SET. (JOB IS NOT HELD)
*  2     AFTER CONVERSION, HASPXEQ RE-QUES THE JOB TO THE $SETUP QUE
*          IF A /*SETUP HAS BEEN FLAGGED AS PRESENT AND $POSTS SETUP.
*  3     WHEN POSTED FOR WORK,  THE SETUP PROCESSOR SEARCHES THE $SETUP
*          QUEUE FOR A JOB.
*  4     WHEN A JOB IS FOUND, THE JCL IMAGE DATA SET FOR THE JOB IS
*          READ, SEARCHING FOR /*SETUP CARDS.
*  5     FOR EACH DETECTED /*SETUP, A MESSAGE IS ISSUED TO THE
*          TAPE/DISK LIBRARY CONSOLE.
*  6     IF A DSNAME IS SPECIFIED IN THE SETUP, A CATALOG SEARCH IS
*          PERFORMED (VIA SUBTASK) AND THE VOLUME SERIAL IS ALSO
*          ADDED TO THE MESSAGE TEXT.
*  7     IF A DSN SPECIFICATION RESULTS IN A DISK VOLSER, THE JOB
           CLASS IS CHANGED TO 'R' IF THE CLASS IS NOW 'S'.
*  8     AFTER ALL SETUPS HAVE BEEN PROCESSED, THE JOB IS PLACED
*          IN HOLD AND RE-QUED FOR XEQ BY CLASS.
*
